oses referred to in point (h) of paragraph 2 when those data are processed by or under the responsibility of a professional subject to the obligation of professional secrecy under Union or Member State law or rules established by national competent bodies or by another person also subject to an obligation of secrecy under Union or Member State law or rules established by national competent bodies.\n\nMember States may maintain or introduce further conditions, including limitations, with regard to the processing of genetic data, biometric data or data concerning health.	9	{"extracted_at": "2025-02-08T13:11:20.934403", "is_definitions": false}	2025-02-08 21:11:21.08534+00	2025-02-08 21:11:21.08534+00
