onal organisation, including the identification of that third country or international organisation and, in the case of transfers referred to in the second subparagraph of Article 49 (1) , the documentation of suitable safeguards;\n\n(d) where possible, a general description of the technical and organisational security measures referred to in Article 32 (1) .\n\nThe records referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 shall be in writing, including in electronic form.\n\nThe controller or the processor and, where applicable, the controller's or the processor's representative, shall make the record available to the supervisory authority on request.\n\nThe obligations referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 shall not apply to an enterprise or an organisation employing fewer than 250 persons unless the processing it carries out is likely to result in a risk to the rights and freedoms of data subjects, the processing is not occasional, or the processing includes special categories of data as referred to in Article 9 (1) or personal data relating to criminal convictions and offences referred to in Article 10.	30	{"extracted_at": "2025-02-08T13:11:20.961546", "is_definitions": false}	2025-02-08 21:11:21.08534+00	2025-02-08 21:11:21.08534+00
