9c8c688d-3d20-4070-8203-1992e542f40e	0d43f0bf-0253-4898-8411-a3cebb042982	3	\N	In the cases referred to in paragraph 2 of this Article, the supervisory authority shall inform the lead supervisory authority without delay on that matter. Within a period of three weeks after being informed the lead supervisory authority shall decide whether or not it will handle the case in accordance with the procedure provided in Article 60, taking into account whether or not there is an establishment of the controller or processor in the Member State of which the supervisory authority informed it.	{"chapeau_count": 1, "total_elements": 1, "subparagraph_count": 0}	2025-02-08 21:11:21.08534+00	2025-02-08 21:11:21.08534+00
